    <stitle>STEERING COLUMN ASSEMBLY, TILT - REMOVE - STEERING COLUMN ASSEMBLY</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc id="hl0500802" svcproctype="remove" graphiccount="1">
        <title>STEERING COLUMN ASSEMBLY</title>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove battery negative cable.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Mark position of universal joint on universal joint assembly lower shaft (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f0500804">Figure 4</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f0500804" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g0500804" filename="../figg05/G0500804.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 4. Steering Column Removal</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1>1. HORN BUTTON COVER</callout1>
                    <callout1>2. NUT</callout1>
                    <callout1>3. STEERING WHEEL</callout1>
                    <callout1>4. STEERING COLUMN</callout1>
                    <callout1>5. LOWER STEERING SHAFT</callout1>
                    <callout1>6. DASH REINFORCEMENT</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the pinch bolt that secures the tilt column shaft to the universal joint assembly.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Disconnect the horn and turn signal wiring from the wiring harness. Disconnect the dimmer
                switch wiring from the steering column wiring bundle.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove bolts, nuts and lockwashers that attach the column to the dash reinforcement.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the steering column from vehicle.</para>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
